				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Oh- are those yours?<a name="32664"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 3 04 8:59 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>gah!  Why oh why oh why are some people just so darned thick headed?  
<br />

<br />
I was in the Wakening Lands kiting panthers for my cleric.  She is a tailor, and it really makes alot more sense to have the 65 bard out there hunting panthers than the 49 cleric eh?  When I zoned in, no one was in WL, so I could kite away with impunity.
<br />

<br />
I am not a greedy bard- I know how to share.  However, if there is no one else in the zone, then I will certainly slay everything I can see!  So that's what I was doing.  I had killed of half my swarm (it wasn't a huge one, only about 20 or so to begin with) and along comes holgresh who I decide needs to die now on the off chance that it roots me.  
<br />

<br />
So I'm DoTing him down, and when I run one circle, I look, and a wood elf does a crowd dive into my remaining panthers.  I do a quick /who in the zone.  Myself and a 55 ranger are the only ones here.  My holgresh is dead, and the ranger has managed to taunt the rest of the swarm on to him because I only had proximity aggro on them.
<br />

<br />
I say &quot;HEY!&quot;
<br />
no answer
<br />
&quot;HEY!!!&quot;
<br />
&quot;oh are these yours?&quot;
<br />
&quot;um... yes!&quot;
<br />

<br />
This is where I'm thinking &quot;Oh no- I'm just standing here in a pile of panther corpses with a small swarm of panthers around me.  Here- you take them.&quot; <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
What in the world is this guy thinking?  65 bard, swarm of critters, oh I'll go jump in the middle of them being the 55 ranger that I am.
<br />

<br />
Whatever he did to get aggro, they wanted him, his level maybe?  I dunno, but the only way I could get aggro was to actually damage each one, and dangit, in a herd of black, it was hard to target each one especially because the ranger began to realize that 10 panthers were going to eat him alive and he began to run around saying &quot;take them back!&quot;
<br />

<br />
I just fought the one that came back to me and let him have his pack.  Once he found his way to the zone they eventually made their way back to me anyway.  Wasted my time though.  grrrr.  Grow a brain please.</span></td>
